<DATE>09/10/2009</DATE>
<AUTHOR>S V</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>Have had this car for 6 months and about 7000 miles. It is an incredible value and I have no regrets on the purchase. The car is refined yet powerful in a way that no other sedan in the 20's (real world price) can touch. The torque is always available and free flowing and lets the car cruise at highway speeds effortlessly. Mileage is acceptable on the freeway, quite bad (10 or so mpg) in stop and go. The interior doesn't match the exterior style-wise and there are a few cheap plastic bits but I can live with it and the styling is nowhere near as tacky as some past Pontiacs. Big flaw is passenger seat does not go back far enough for taller people. Car was delivered with warped rotors.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Other than the fake hood scoops and the just so-so rims, I love the looks of this car. The lines and proportioning are perfect. The interior is extremely comfortable for long trips. And of course the power...for what I paid nothing on the planet can touch it. Variable displacement helps the MPG.</FAVORITE>
